The draw for the quarter-final of this season’s FA Cup will be conducted on Wednesday night. Arsenal and Chelsea have already booked their spot in the last eight. The Gunners beat Portsmouth 2-0 on Monday, while the Blues also saw off the Premier League leaders 2-0 on Tuesday. Tottenham host Norwich on Wednesday, while Manchester United clash with Derby County in ties that are yet to be played. The FA Cup quarter-final draw will take place after Manchester City’s match against Sheffield Wednesday. Ball numbers:
1 Sheffield Wednesday or Manchester City 2 Reading or Sheffield United 3 Chelsea 4 West Bromwich Albion or Newcastle United 5 Leicester City or Birmingham City 6 Derby County or Manchester United 7 Tottenham Hotspur or Norwich City 8 Arsenal